** About You **   
  
The most important aspect of any new role for us is ensuring we get the right
person onboard. We value diverse ideas and skillsets, and we want to ensure
that our newest team-member will be recognised for their unique skills,
ability and creativity.  
  
We currently have a ** Permanent Full-Time ** opportunity for a Yardi Systems
Analyst to support our finance team in the operation of our Yardi ERP
management platform.  
  
Our ideal candidate will be interested in learning new systems and have a
desire to apply themselves and solve issues. You will also be looking to
utilise knowledge beyond the system, to how the platform can best be utilised
within the business architecture and provide benefits to the users.  
  
** About the role **   
  
As the Yardi Systems Analyst, you will be responsible for supporting our Yardi
Specialist to ensure all business-critical requirements are met in relation to
the Yardi Platform. You'll work across a range of teams within the business to
ensure the system is being used consistently and confidently across our AU
portfolio.  
  
This role will see you both maintaining our system while also developing your
knowledge to identify issues and potential improvements. You'll be attending
user group and professional development meetings to actively contribute to
both your development and your understanding of the platform.  
  
You will need to have an eye for detail and be adaptable to the varying
situations you'll come across. It is essential that you have experience in a
Systems Administration role, ideally in the property industry. Any experience
with financial systems such as SAP, MRI and JD Edwards will be beneficial.  
  
